Based on the documentation, here's what I found about relational attributes in ARFF:

Relational attributes are defined with a specific syntax:

```
@attribute [name] relational
  [further attribute definitions]
@end [name]
```

The documentation provides a brief example from the MUSK1 dataset:

```
@attribute molecule_name {MUSK-jf78,...,NON-MUSK-199}
@attribute bag relational
  @attribute f1 numeric
  ...
  @attribute f166 numeric
@end bag
@attribute class {0,1}
```

In the data section, relational data must be "enclosed within double quotes". An example instance is shown as:

`MUSK-188,"42,...,30",1`

The documentation notes that relational attributes are "for multi-instance data (for future use)", suggesting this is a somewhat experimental feature in Weka.

The text does not provide explicit details about handling newlines within relational attribute data beyond the requirement of enclosing the data in double quotes.

